              <h2>How Does AGM Technology Redefine Car Batteries?</h2>
              <p>
                Traditional flooded lead-acid batteries, the workhorses powering
                vehicles for decades, have served us well. However, they have
                limitations. AGM technology takes car batteries to a whole new
                level by addressing these limitations and offering significant
                advantages.
              </p>
              <p>
                Instead of liquid acid, an AGM battery uses a special fiberglass
                mat soaked with an electrolyte solution. It holds the
                electrolyte in place, preventing spills or leaks, even if your
                car is parked on a hill.
              </p>
              <p>
                Additionally, this battery is completely sealed, which
                eliminates the hassle of checking or adding water. This saves
                you time and ensures optimal performance.
              </p>
