                    alt="Lower Self-discharge"
                  />
                </div>
                <h3>Lower Self-discharge</h3>
                <p>
                  A regular flooded lead-acid battery might lose around 8% of
                  its charge in time. An AGM battery, however, is much better at
                  holding its charge. It loses about 4% per month at room
                  temperature (25°C). This lower self-discharge rate gets even
                  better in cooler weather and slightly worse in very hot
                  climates. 
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-xl-5">
              <div class="content">
                <div class="image show-on-small-devices">
